Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 625 056 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19 30 August 2020 As of today, a cumulative total of 625 056 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded with 2 505 new cases identified Case data Province Total cases for 30 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 86060 13,7 Free State 37557 5,9 Gauteng 209648 33,5 KwaZulu-Natal 112726 18,0 Limpopo 13167 2,1 Mpumalanga 24132 3,8 North West 25240 4,0 Northern Cape 10568 1,6 Western Cape 105908 16,9 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 625056 100,0 The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 674 872 with 21 902 new tests conducted since the last report. Total Deaths and Recoveries Regrettably, we report 47 more COVID-19 related deaths: 3 from KwaZulu-Natal,16 from Gauteng, 7 from Eastern Cape, 7 from Western Cape, 3 from Free State and 11 from Mpumalanga. This brings the total number of COVID-19 related deaths to 14028. We extend our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers that treated the deceased patients. Our recoveries now stand at 538 604 which translates to a recovery rate of 86% Province Total Deaths Total Recoveries Active Cases Eastern Cape 2876 81373 1811 Free State 693 23092 13772 Gauteng 3572 181299 24777 KwaZulu-Natal 2138 95653 14935 Limpopo 179 12103 885 Mpumalanga 341 22563 1228 North West 240 18492 6508 Northern Cape 120 6972 3476 Western Cape 3869 97057 4982 Total 14028 538604 72374 Issued by Department of Health, 31 August 2020 eval(ez_write_tag([[336,280],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_1',112,'0','0'])); 